"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105871","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-10","<p><strong>For financial years 2010-11 and 2011-12 external lawyers were retained through the Treasury Solicitor’s Department. Since 2012, DCMS has not incurred any costs in legal fees regarding the release of information requested under the Freedom of Information Act. </strong></p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-11-10T15:47:11.1886374Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105871/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105871/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105871/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much his Department has spent on legal fees over prevention of release of information requested by Freedom of Information requests since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213103"
