"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105875","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-11","<p>The majority of mobile telephones supplied to the Ministry of Defence (MOD) are provided by Vodafone through an enabling arrangement through the Defence Fixed Telecommunications Service (DFTS) contract with BT. A very small number (less than 1%) of mobile telephones are procured outside this arrangement to meet local operational demands, typically at MOD establishments overseas. Until July 2014, the procurement of iPhones required purchase authorisation outside the scope of the DFTS catalogue but, since then, iPhones have been ordered by routine processes via the DFTS catalogue. Monthly network access charges for iPhones are greater than basic mobile telephones. Expenditure on iPhone accounts via the DFTS contract is in the attached table.</p><p> </p><p>It should be noted that iPhones purchased prior to Jan 2010 continue to incur network access charges in the reporting period. The current cost differential is £5 for a basic mobile phone per month and £11.23 for an iPhone.</p><p> </p><p>The annual expenditure on iPhone purchases and network acccess charges via the DFTS contract since January 2010 to October 2014 are shown in the attached table:</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-11T17:41:58.332069Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105875/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105875/answer","213153 - Expenditure on iPhones.doc","213153 - Expenditure on iPhones.doc","213153 - MOD Expenditure on iPhones","213153 - MOD Expenditure on iPhones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105875/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent on iPhones in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105876","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-17","<p>To date, the Afghanistan Government has made no formal representations to the Secretary of State on the use of the Royal Air Force to provide close air support to the Afghan National Security Forces.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","217756 ; 218556","2014-12-17T17:35:53.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105876/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105876/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105876/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105876/answer/previousversion/29876","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent representations he has received from the Afghan government on the use of the Royal Air Force to provide close air support for the Afghan National Security forces.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","213144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105877","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-10","<p>The NATO train, advise and assist mission will have around 12,000 personnel from NATO allies and partners in 2015. The UK will contribute a few hundred military personnel.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-10T17:40:12.915226Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105877/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105877/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105877/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assets and how many personnel will take part in Operation Resolute Support.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","213145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105878","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-03","<p>The Civil Service Commission recognises that in some circumstances it may be right to allow appointments to be made outside of the principle of selection on merit on the basis of fair and open competition. Those exceptions are designed to provide a flexible way of recruiting staff where this is necessary in the interests of the Civil Service; for example, to meet a short-term need for specialist skills.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested is contained in the table below.The Ministry of Defence does not hold records of appointments by exception prior to Financial Year 2012-13. For data protection purposes, name of individuals appointed to roles cannot be disclosed.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>No. of appointments</strong></p><p><strong>made by exception</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>134</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>169</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15 (to 31 October)</p></td><td><p>95</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-12-03T16:49:03.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105878/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105878/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105878/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105878/answer/previousversion/29877","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions his Department has made appointments by exception since 2010; and who was appointed for each such post.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105879","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Ministry of Justice (MOJ) publishes a quarterly statistics bulletin recording Freedom of Information responses from all Government Departments, including the Ministry of Defence. The bulletin includes tables showing how many requests were granted in full, or resulted in some or all information being withheld. The MOJ statistics bulletin can be found at: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-17T16:55:35.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105879/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105879/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Freedom of Information requests his Department has declined to answer in full since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213083"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105880","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-10","<p>Since 2008 the Royal Navy has contributed to the coalition counter-piracy and counter-terrorism operations commanded by the European Union (EU), NATO, and Combined Maritime Forces (CMF). This has included the contribution of assets; and the provision of the Operational Headquarters and Operational Commander for the EU’s Operation ATALANTA; the NATO Maritime Commander and Maritime Headquarters that has overall command of Operation OCEAN SHIELD; and the Deputy Commander and supporting staff for the CMF. In addition, the Royal Navy maintains a constant presence, including at least one frigate or destroyer, in the Gulf region. Anti-piracy and anti-terrorism measures off the Horn of Africa, in the Gulf of Aden, and in the Arabian Gulf are among a number of concurrent tasks carried out by the Royal Navy and supporting assets, and expenditure incurred on these operations is not identified separately. The common costs (ie those shared by EU and NATO members that are additional to the national contribution of the operation) for the EU and NATO are as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Operation ATALANTA:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Calendar Year</p></td><td><p>£ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>8.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>8.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>7.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>8.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>7.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Operation OCEAN SHIELD:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Calendar Year</p></td><td><p>£ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>0.327</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>0.568</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>0.850</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>0.450</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>0.830</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","213123","2014-11-10T17:39:07.6865632Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105880/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105880/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105880/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Piracy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost was of the UK's contribution to Operation Atalanta in each financial year from 2008-09 to 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","213122"
