"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105884","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-20","<table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" rowspan="5"> </td><td colspan="6" rowspan="5"><p>I refer the hon. Member to the Answer my right hon. Friend the Minister of State for the Cabinet Office (Francis Maude) gave him on 10 November 2014, to Question UIN 213040.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-20T16:57:10.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105884/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105884/answer","HOC 213040 10 November 2014.doc","HOC 213040 10 November 2014.doc","Hansard Extract 10 November 2014 ","Hansard Extract 10 November 2014 ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105884/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions his Department has had requests for appointments by exception to the Senior Civil Service turned down by the Civil Service Commission since 2010; and who was appointed for each such post.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105885","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him on 1 September 2014, (Official Report, column 95W). Since that answer, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) has spent a further £17,470.52 in 2013-14, bringing the total in that financial year to £66,319.58. In the current financial year, to date the MOD has spent £14,471.00.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-17T16:59:56.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105885/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105885/answer","20141106-PQW2014-06651-John Woodcock MP-Legal Fees for FOI final[1].doc","20141106-PQW2014-06651-John Woodcock MP-Legal Fees for FOI final[1].doc","20140901 - Hansard extract on FOI","20140901 - Hansard extract on FOI","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105885/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on legal fees over prevention of release of information requested by Freedom of Information requests since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105886","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>There are currently 926 Service Family accommodation properties in Colchester. On 30 September 2014, 124 of these were unoccupied.</p><p>Of these 124 unoccupied, 50 were three-bedroomed and 29 were four-bedroomed properties.</p><p>The Ministry of Defence always maintains a management margin of vacant properties, in order to ensure that properties are available for incoming families and to allow for essential maintenance.</p><p>36 of the 124 properties have since been allocated to families. They are due to move in these in the near future.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-17T16:57:56.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105886/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105886/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105886/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many vacant army dwellings there were on 30 September 2014 in Colchester; and how many such properties had (a) three and (b) four bedrooms.","false","Biography information for Sir Bob Russell","Colchester","Sir Bob Russell","213127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105887","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-02","<p>The Ministry of Defence operates a Minor Award Scheme, which recognises performance over and above that is normally required in a specific task. The table below shows the number of awards and their total value for Financial Years (FY) 2012-13 and 2013-14. The information is not held by calendar year.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>FY 2012-13</p></td><td><p>Total Value</p></td><td><p>FY 2013-14</p></td><td><p>Total Value</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of Awards</p></td><td><p>5,348</p></td><td><p>£344,471.14</p></td><td><p>3,701</p></td><td><p>£284,272.43</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of awards does not equate to the number of officials who received them; awards can be made to individuals or teams of individuals.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-12-02T16:26:42.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105887/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105887/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105887/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105887/answer/previousversion/29873","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Instant Rewards of what value were given to his Department's officials in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105888","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>The Government is committed to revising the Strategic Defence and Security Strategy in 2015.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-11-25T16:58:44.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105888/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105888/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105888/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Strategic Defence and Security Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will bring forward the timescale for the revision of the Strategic Defence and Security Review.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Mr Jeffrey M. Donaldson","212981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105889","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the debate on the Military Covenant in Northern Ireland on 22 October 2014 (Official Report, columns 971-1004), during which I advised the House that practically all of the measures in the Covenant, more than 90%, now extend to Northern Ireland, or will do so soon.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-25T17:02:45.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105889/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105889/answer","Armed Forces Covenant 22 October 2014.doc","Armed Forces Covenant 22 October 2014.doc","Hansard Extract 22 October 2014","Hansard Extract 22 October 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105889/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Armed Forces Covenant: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of the commitments in the Armed Forces Covenant have been implemented in Northern Ireland to date.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Mr Jeffrey M. Donaldson","212982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105890","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-24","<p>Defence provides support to the civil powers in defence of UK-owned maritime offshore installations through the provision of a guaranteed maritime capability, in excess of that which the civil powers can provide for themselves. This ranges from advice, through surveillance and reconnaissance to military intervention.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-24T16:56:05.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105890/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105890/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105890/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Offshore Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which military assets are tasked with the defence of UK-owned maritime offshore installations.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","212956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105891","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>The Ministry Of Defence provides support to the civil powers by protecting UK-owned maritime offshore installations; routine bilateral engagement takes place with those nations (including Norway and our NATO partners) which have an interest in these arrangements.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-25T16:49:08.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105891/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105891/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105891/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105891/answer/previousversion/29874","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Offshore Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what arrangements his Department has in place with (a) NATO and (b) Norway for the defence of maritime offshore installations in the North Sea.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","212957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105892","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>The River Class Offshore Patrol Vessels HMS MERSEY, HMS TYNE and HMS SEVERN form the Royal Navy's Fishery Protection Squadron, which provides the Royal Navy's contribution to fishery protection duties within the United Kingdom's exclusive economic zone.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-25T16:57:59.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105892/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105892/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105892/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Fisheries: Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which military assets are tasked with fisheries protection within the UK's exclusive economic zone.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","212959"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105893","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>All of the UK’s military assets are available for the defence of the British Overseas Territories, subject to availability and operational requirements.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Defence undertakes regular assessments of potential military threats to all overseas territories to ensure that we retain an appropriate level of defensive capability to address any such threats.</p><p> </p><p>As at 5 November 2014, in the attached the following military assets were present in the Overseas Territories and tasked with the defence of the Territory in question.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-25T16:50:15.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105893/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105893/answer","212958 - Military Assets presents in Overseas Territories.doc ; HOC211278.doc","212958 - Military Assets presents in Overseas Territories.doc ; HOC211278.doc","Military Assets present in Overseas Territories ; 211278 - Q n A Extract on Overseas Territories","Military Assets present in Overseas Territories ; 211278 - Q n A Extract on Overseas Territories","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105893/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105893/answer/previousversion/29871","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","British Overseas Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which military assets are tasked with the defence of British Overseas Territories.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","212958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105894","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-06","<p>On 11 October 2014 the UK and Bahrain signed a Defence Co-Operation Accord to provide a framework for existing and future defence engagement activity, including training and capacity- building, in order to enhance the stability of the wider region. The Accord complements Memoranda of Understanding covering Status of Forces, Defence Equipment Cooperation and Exercises and Training. In addition, we have had a long-standing presence in Bahrain, with continuous Royal Navy patrols in the Gulf since the 1980s protecting Britain's interests.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-06T17:33:15.3122281Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105894/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105894/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105894/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-03","Bahrain","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what defence agreements exist between the UK and Bahrain.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","212871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105895","Department for Education","false","2014-11-10","<p>Local authority (LA) maintained schools’ funding is allocated per financial year, whereas academy school funding is allocated on the basis of the academic year.</p><p>In the financial year 2012-13 the amount spent on supply teachers<a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/212870-%20Nicholas%20Brown/Draft/212870%20QA%205.11.14.docx#_ftn1" target="_blank">[1]</a> in LA maintained schools in England was £893,389,000. The 2013-14 data for LA maintained schools will be available in December. The amount spent on supply teachers in academies<a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/212870-%20Nicholas%20Brown/Draft/212870%20QA%205.11.14.docx#_ftn2" target="_blank">[2]</a> in England in the 2012-13 academic year was £176,384,000. The 2013/14 data for academies will be available in the summer of 2015.</p><p>Academies have responsibilities that maintained schools do not, particularly around services previously provided by the local authority (library services, behavioural support services, audit costs, etc.) and maintenance of capital assets. This can affect what the academy spends its funding on, meaning that an academy, by its nature, is likely to have a different pattern of spend than a maintained school. For this reason, figures for academies and maintained schools are not directly comparable.</p><p>Expenditure on supply teachers in Wales is a devolved matter.</p><p><a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/212870-%20Nicholas%20Brown/Draft/212870%20QA%205.11.14.docx#_ftnref1" target="_blank">[1]</a> Includes salaries and wages for supply teaching staff employed directly by the school, premiums paid to insurers for supply teacher cover and includes costs paid to an agency for teaching staff that have been brought in to cover teacher absence. Includes cover of any period and for all reasons including illness, absence for training, and any leave.</p><p><a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/212870-%20Nicholas%20Brown/Draft/212870%20QA%205.11.14.docx#_ftnref2" target="_blank">[2]</a> The figures quoted for academies only include 1633 Single Academy Trusts and 135 Multi Academy Trusts that returned an accounting return (AR) for at least the full academic year of 2012/13. Multi academy trusts where one or more school within the trust was not open for the full 2012/13 academic year are not included.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-11-10T16:59:02.2652358Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105895/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105895/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105895/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Supply Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much was spent on supply teachers in England and Wales in the academic year 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","212870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105896","Department for Education","false","2014-11-10","<p>The data for initial teacher training (ITT) allocations for School Direct and HE providers over the last 5 years is shown in the table below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HE providers</p></td><td><p>28,669</p></td><td><p>28,841</p></td><td><p>26,790</p></td><td><p>23,095</p></td><td><p>22,224</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>School Direct</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>772</p></td><td><p>9,586</p></td><td><p>15,254</p></td><td><p>17,609</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-11-10T17:23:23.1321084Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105896/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105896/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105896/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many places were distributed in the initial allocations for initial teacher training trainees to School Direct and HE providers in (a) 2011-12, (b) 2012-13, (c) 2013-14, (d) 2014-15 and (e) 2015-16; and what the target number of trainees estimated by the National College of Teaching and Leadership, the National College for School Leadership and the Teaching Agency was in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","212886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105897","Department for Education","false","2014-11-10","<p>The academic year 2013/14 was the first time School Direct information was available in the Initial Teacher Training (ITT) Census.<a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/212887-%20Nic%20Dakin/Draft/212887%20QA%20Version%204%20-%205.11.14%20FINAL.docx#_ftn1" target="_blank">[1]</a> The information is published online at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2013-to-2014</a></p><p>Information from the 2013/14 ITT Census shows that 6,580 new entrants were recruited to School Direct initial teacher training places. Of these, 2,890 (44%) were recruited to primary places (i.e. primary schools) and the remaining 3,690 (56%) to secondary schools.</p><p>The 2014/15 Census will be published on 27 November 2014.</p><p><a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/212887-%20Nic%20Dakin/Draft/212887%20QA%20Version%204%20-%205.11.14%20FINAL.docx#_ftnref1" target="_blank">[1]</a> There was a small number of School Direct providers in the academic year 2012-13; however the data was aggregated for publication.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-11-10T17:02:11.2903363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105897/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105897/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105897/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Teachers: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many trainee teachers were recruited in the initial allocations to School Direct in each subject to (a) primary and (b) secondary schools in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","212887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105898","Department for Education","false","2014-11-06","<p>The Department for Education collects information from local authorities on the number of school places in state-funded primary and secondary schools and local authorities’ own pupil forecasts as part of the annual School Capacity Collection. The most recent data available relates to the position at May 2013, with primary forecasts through to 2017/18, and is published online at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-capacity-academic-year-2012-to-2013" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-capacity-academic-year-2012-to-2013</a></p><p>The Department has estimated that Warrington local authority needs 270 additional primary places to meet demand in 2015/16. Warrington local authority has reported that there are 980 new places planned for delivery between 2013/14 and 2015/16. This information, along with technical notes, is published in the Local Authority Basic Need Scorecards which is published online at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/primary-school-places-local-authority-basic-need-scorecards" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/primary-school-places-local-authority-basic-need-scorecards</a></p><p>The Department provides capital funding to local authorities in line with the estimated level of need in each local authority. Warrington has been allocated a total of £6 million for the period 2011-2015 and a further £8.6 million for 2015-2017 to help create the additional school places that will be needed by September 2017.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-11-06T16:21:01.5325676Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105898/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105898/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Primary Education: Warrington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the requirement for primary school places in Warrington in the next five years.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","212903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105899","Department for Education","false","2014-11-11","<p>In 2013/14, the latest year for which data is available, there were 12,500 students enrolled in those new sixth forms which had opened between 2011/12 and 2013/14. The Department for Education does not have records for new sixth forms prior to 2011.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-11-11T17:44:23.3356446Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105899/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105899/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Sixth Form Education: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many students are enrolled in those school and academy sixth forms that have opened since 2010.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","212988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105900","Department for Education","false","2014-11-10","<p>In 2013, 3,954 instant rewards were issued to officials of the Department for Education. The total value of such rewards was £132,140, giving an average value of £33.42.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In 2014 to date (4 November), 4,825 instant rewards have been issued. The total value of instant rewards this year has been £200,245, giving an average value of £41.50.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The instant reward scheme is funded from the staff pay bill (not in addition to it). Each year 0.1% of the pay budget is set aside to pay for instant reward vouchers and any associated tax and National Insurance.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-11-10T16:13:57.3166527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105900/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105900/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many Instant Rewards of what value were given to her Department's officials in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105901","Department for Education","false","2014-11-10","<p>Since 2010, the Civil Service Commission has not turned down any requests made by the Department for Education to appoint a Senior Civil Servant by exception.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-11-10T16:15:27.9978822Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105901/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105901/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, on how many occasions her Department has had requests for appointments by exception to the Senior Civil Service turned down by the Civil Service Commission since 2010; and who was appointed for each such post.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105902","Department for Education","false","2014-11-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend, the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Children and Families on 21 July 2014 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-07-16/206217/" target="_blank">206217</a>.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-11-10T15:46:18.9936433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105902/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105902/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much her Department has spent on legal fees over prevention of release of information requested by Freedom of Information requests since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105903","Department for Education","false","2014-11-11","<p>In 2013/14, the latest year for which data is available, there were 3,000 students enrolled in those 16-19 academy and free schools that opened since 2010.[1]</p><p> </p><p>This figure does not include those that opened in 2014 as there is no student data yet available. The data sources used are the School Census 2013/14 S02 and Individualised Learner Record 2013/14 R14. The figures include funded learners only.</p><p> </p><p>[1] Figures are rounded to the nearest 100.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-11-11T15:55:14.6098147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105903/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105903/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Academies: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many students are enrolled in those 16-19 academy and free schools that have opened since 2010.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","212989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105904","Department for Education","false","2014-11-06","<p>In the 2013/14 academic year we allocated extra School Direct requests, as well as allowing relinquishments. The School Direct initial allocations were 9,441 and the final allocations 9,586, meaning the net change for School Direct was an extra 145 places allocated throughout the year.</p><p>The initial and final allocations for the 2014/15 academic year are both published on the NCTL/Gov.uk website:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2013-to-2014-final" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2013-to-2014-final</a></p><p>The Department for Education does not hold information on relinquishments in the format requested. The National College for Teaching and Leadership plans to publish updated management information by the end of December 2014. This will include line by line initial and final allocations by school (and provider) by subject and will enable the calculation of relinquishments.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-11-06T16:22:05.7560791Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105904/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105904/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many places from the initial allocation were relinquished by School Direct in the 2013-14 admissions year.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","213003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105905","Department for Education","false","2014-11-06","<p>The initial allocations for School Direct for the academic year were 15,254.</p><p>The initial allocations for the 2014/15 academic year were published in October 2013 and are published online at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2014-to-2015</a></p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-11-06T16:17:35.3655632Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105905/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105905/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Teachers: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many places were allocated to School Direct for recruitment in the 2014-15 acacemic year.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","213004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105906","Department for Education","false","2014-11-10","<p>Quarterly and annual statistics on Freedom of Information requests received by the Department for Education, including the number of requests in which all requested information was released in full, is set out in the table below. This information is published online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Requests received</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Resolvable requests [1]</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Resolvable requests granted in full</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>880</p></td><td><p>733</p></td><td><p>549 (75%)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>1,149</p></td><td><p>937</p></td><td><p>590 (63%)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1,309</p></td><td><p>1,038</p></td><td><p>686 (66%)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>1,759</p></td><td><p>1,354</p></td><td><p>931 (69%)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014 (Q1 and Q2)</p></td><td><p>961</p></td><td><p>710</p></td><td><p>399 (56%)</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>[1] Resolvable – requests in which it was possible to give a substantive decision on whether to release the information being sought; for example, excluding requests where the information sought was not held or further clarification was necessary.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-11-10T15:43:22.2626357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105906/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105906/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many Freedom of Information requests her Department has declined to answer in full since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213084"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105907","Department for Education","false","2014-11-10","<p>Since 1 April 2010, the Department for Education has made 1,722 appointments by exception. The numbers of appointments are set out in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p><p> </p></td><td><p>Exceptions</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>32</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>216</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>1353</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>62</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1/04/14 to date</p></td><td><p>59</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Of these exceptions, 1,565 were the result of a programme to reform the Department’s Arm’s Length Bodies (ALBs) which gave staff the right of transfer into the Department and its new Executive Agencies.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-11-10T16:18:18.1668058Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105907/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105907/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, on how many occasions her Department has made appointments by exception since 2010; and who was appointed for each such post.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105908","Department for Education","false","2014-11-10","<p>The Department for Education has spent the following amounts on iPhones in each year since 2010:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Costs (£)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>1,188</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1,836</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>31,038</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In 2011 and 2012 a total of six iPhones were purchased for staff with accessibility requirements where the standard departmental mobile device (Blackberry) would not meet their needs. There was no requirement to purchase any further devices in 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The significant increase in 2014 was due to the implementation of a new mobile working pilot utilising ‘GOOD’ Technology (a secure IT mobility solution) where iPhones were the preferred device and 57 devices were purchased as part of the pilot. Following an evaluation, the pilot has now been discontinued, and the Department is in discussions with Vodafone regarding the return of these devices and recuperation of costs. The above costs include the purchase of an Apple iPhone device with live SIM card. The models purchased were a combination of iPhone 4, 5 and 5S.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-11-10T16:23:48.8139403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105908/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105908/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-03","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much her Department spent on iPhones in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213154"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105909","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-10","<p>The Department of Energy and Climate Change has spent £400 in 2011, £800 in 2012, and £400 in 2013 on iPhones for testing purposes.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-10T14:05:50.9212214Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105909/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105909/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much his Department spent on iPhones in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105910","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-07","<p>Under the Civil Service Recruitment Principles, DECC has only utilised the exceptions of short term/temporary appointments, secondments and transfers of organisations into the Civil Service – TUPE. Please note DECC only holds data from November 2010. Since this date we have made 150 exception appointments under these categories. The names of those appointed at grade 6 and below (or equivalent) are withheld under the Data Protection Act 1998. Additionally, DECC’s systems do not always record the equivalent grade for those seconded from industry and therefore we are unable to release these names under the Data Protection Act 1998. Our records confirm that we have appointed four members of the SCS as an exception – Peter Boyd, Miles Bradbury, Gordon Dunfield-Prayero and David MacKay.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-07T12:48:29.481972Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105910/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105910/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, on how many occasions his Department has made appointments by exception since 2010; and who was appointed for each such post.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105911","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-05","<p>There have been 9 people from energy companies who have had periods of secondment in the Department of Energy and Climate Change (DECC) in the period May 2010 to date.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-05T15:57:31.0912177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105911/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105911/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many employees of energy companies have been seconded to jobs in his Department since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","213126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105912","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-07","<p>Between January 2010 and September 2014 DECC withheld information on 1250 occasions.</p><p>Statistics on the Freedom of Information performance of Government Departments since January 2010 are published by the Ministry of Justice. They are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics#2010-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics#2010-2012</a>.</p><p>The published statistics include the numbers of requests received by each Department, the numbers answered in full and where information was partly or fully withheld.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-07T12:49:42.3173899Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105912/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105912/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105912/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many Freedom of Information requests his Department has declined to answer in full since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105913","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-05","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister has appointed advisors and envoys on a number of issues, and determines their remit. This role is entirely separate from the responsibilities of my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-05T15:56:38.4687303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105913/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105913/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the respective remits are of his Department and the Prime Minister's Envoy on Climate Change; and what the relationship between them is.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","212999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105914","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-11","<p>Of the 10,048 approved accreditations, 1,755 were new installations and 8,293 were legacy installations.</p><p> </p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-11T16:44:54.0774172Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105914/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105914/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, pursuant to the Answer of 3 November 2014 to Question 212296, how many of the approved accreditations were (a) new installations lodged after the launch of the domestic renewables heat incentive scheme and (b) legacy installations.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","212998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105915","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-10","<p>Legal advice is not routinely sought on requests under the Freedom of Information Act 2000. Where it is, the Department does not calculate the cost of internal legal advice as opposed to the cost of such advice on other matters. The Department obtains external litigation services from the Treasury Solicitor’s Department, including in relation to appeals under the Freedom of Information Act 2000. In 2013/14, the Department paid the Treasury Solicitor’s Department £18,812 for services concerning appeals under the Act. Figures for other periods since 2010 could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-10T16:06:12.0266036Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105915/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105915/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much his Department has spent on legal fees over prevention of release of information requested by Freedom of Information requests since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213106"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105916","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given today by my hon. Friend the Minister of State for Cabinet Office to Questions 213040 and 213053.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-10T14:07:42.3354866Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105916/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105916/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, on how many occasions his Department has had requests for appointments by exception to the Senior Civil Service turned down by the Civil Service Commission since 2010; and who was appointed for each such post.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105917","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-07","<p>The Department has taken the term Instant Rewards to mean non-pay awards. Non pay awards are used as a quick way of acknowledging achievements by members of staff.</p><p>(a) During 2013, 623 awards were made with a total value of £15k.</p><p>(b) In the period January to June 2014, 230 awards have been made with a total value of £5k.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-07T12:51:05.033066Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105917/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105917/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many Instant Rewards of what value were given to his Department's officials in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105918","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-06","<p>On 28 October, National Grid published its annual Winter Outlook 2014 report, which analyses the current level of security of electricity supply in Great Britain. This includes an estimate of peak electricity demand for this winter, but no separate assessment is published for businesses or data centres.</p><p>In order to ensure security of supply for all businesses, households and industry, National Grid announced it will procure 1.1GW of additional de-rated capacity through Supplemental Balancing Reserve (SBR) and Demand Side Balancing Reserve (DSBR) for the winter of 2014/15.</p><p>DECC supports the decisive action taken by National Grid and Ofgem which will mean we have secure electricity supplies, even with further unexpected outages or a very cold winter.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-11-06T16:11:16.9282806Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105918/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105918/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Energy Supply","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment he has made of the security of the electricity supply for (a) businesses and (b) data centres in winter 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Huppert","Cambridge","Dr Julian Huppert","212978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105919","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-06","<p>On 28 October National Grid announced that it will procure 1.1 GW of additional de-rated capacity though Supplemental Balancing Reserve (SBR) and Demand Side Balancing Reserve (DSBR) for the winter of 2014/15. DECC supports the decisive action taken by National Grid and Ofgem and views the amount procured as a sensible and prudent step in order to provide the necessary degree of resilience for times of very high demand.</p><p>This action will increase capacity margins from around 4% to over 6%; a higher level than we had between 2005/06 and 2007/8 and well within the Government’s reliability standard.</p><p>This means that we will continue to benefit from secure electricity supplies even with further unexpected outages or a very cold winter.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-11-06T16:08:14.7575935Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105919/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105919/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Energy Supply","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps he is taking to reduce the risk of electricity blackouts during winter 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","212922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105920","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-11","<p>In August this year, the Department confirmed a grant award under the Marine Energy Array Deployment fund of up to £10m for the development of the world’s first tidal stream array project in the Pentland Firth.</p><p>Tidal energy projects may also receive support under the Renewables Obligation and through applying for a Contract for Difference.</p><p>In October 2010, the Government published the conclusions of a 2-year feasibility study into tidal power on the Severn estuary, including a regional economic impact assessment. While the Government concluded it did not see a strategic case for public investment in a tidal energy scheme in the Severn estuary, the outcome of the feasibility study does not preclude a privately financed scheme. The document can be downloaded at the following web-link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/1-severn-tidal-power-feasibility-study-conclusions-and-summary-report" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/1-severn-tidal-power-feasibility-study-conclusions-and-summary-report</a>.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-11T11:20:39.8595282Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105920/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105920/answer","Severn Tidal Power Feasibility Study Conclusions and Summary Report - 15 Oct.pdf","Severn Tidal Power Feasibility Study Conclusions and Summary Report - 15 Oct.pdf","Severn Tidal Power Feasibility 15 Oct 2014","Severn Tidal Power Feasibility 15 Oct 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105920/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-03","Tidal Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what plans his Department has to develop tidal power technology around the UK; and what investment he plans to allocate for such projects.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","212885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105921","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-05","<p>The Secretary of State met with a number of Welsh farming organisations when she visited the Royal Welsh Show on 21 July. We work closely with farming organisations across the UK and look forward to meeting representatives in due course.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-05T16:11:33.1724207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105921/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105921/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105921/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Agriculture: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when she next plans to meet farming organisations in Wales.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","212928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105922","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-10","<p>The EU Timber Regulation (EUTR) prevents the trade of illegally-harvested timber in the EU by laying obligation on operators who place timber and timber products on the market, and those who subsequently trade in them. It was implemented in the UK by the Timber and Timber Products (Placing on the Market) Regulations in March 2013.</p><p>Independent assessments by the European Commission and WWF rank the UK’s efforts on tackling the trade in illegal timber and our domestic implementation of the EUTR as amongst the best in EU Member States.</p><p>To be fully effective in keeping illegally harvested timber and timber products out of the EU all Member States need to implement the EUTR. We are working closely with the Commission and other Member States on this and have offered to share the UK’s experience with them.</p><p>The review next year will provide us with an opportunity to improve the effectiveness of the EUTR.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-10T12:12:10.7345844Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105922/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105922/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105922/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Timber: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent assessment she has made of the effectiveness of the EU Timber Regulation in preventing the import of illegally-harvested timber; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","212926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105923","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-10","<p>The EU Timber Regulation (EUTR) prevents the trade of illegally-harvested timber in the EU by laying obligation on operators who place timber and timber products on the market and those who subsequently trade in them. It was implemented in the UK by the Timber and Timber Products (Placing on the Market) Regulations in March 2013. The legislation applies to all timber and timber products in scope of the regulation, including illegally-harvested timber from the Brazilian Amazon.</p><p>In the UK, the National Measurement Office (NMO) is the competent authority for the EUTR. The NMO is working closely with its EU counterparts to prevent any shipments of illegal timber entering the EU market.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-10T12:16:02.9737814Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105923/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105923/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105923/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Timber: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent steps she has taken with her EU counterparts to prevent shipments of illegal timber from sawmills in the Brazilian Amazon entering the European market; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","212927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105924","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-06","<p>I chair regular meetings of the Dairy Supply Chain Forum which includes key representatives from the whole of the supply chain, including colleagues from Wales and from the farming industry. The next meeting is on 19 November. It will focus on the key issues and opportunities that the dairy sector is facing, including the latest market situation.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, Defra officials maintain regular contact with their counterparts in Wales on a range of dairy issues.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-11-06T14:04:11.9520141Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105924/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105924/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Milk: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent discussions she has had with farming organisations in Wales about changes in the price of milk.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","212929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105925","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-06","<p>Milk prices are falling as a result of the ban on dairy imports to Russia and falling returns from global commodity markets. Despite these challenges, the long-term outlook for UK dairying remains positive. Over the next decade, the UK dairy industry estimates global demand to rise by 2.5% a year with growing world incomes and an expanding population. UK dairy exports are already at record levels and we will continue to encourage and support our domestic farmers and processors to develop their businesses.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-11-06T15:05:24.6324074Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105925/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105925/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105925/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Milk: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment she has made of the causes of recent changes in the price of milk.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","212930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105926","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-07","<p>The Department does not have or operate an Instant Rewards policy.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-07T14:22:46.9698074Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105926/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105926/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105926/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many Instant Rewards of what value were given to her Department's officials in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105927","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-06","<p>The Department does not hold the information requested. Legal expenditure is not broken down in this way.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-06T14:34:33.3737709Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105927/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105927/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105927/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department has spent on legal fees over prevention of release of information requested by Freedom of Information requests since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213107"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105928","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-10","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer provided today by my Rt. Hon. friend the Member for Horsham to PQs UIN 213043 and 213053.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-10T12:26:15.904108Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105928/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105928/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105928/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, on how many occasions her Department has had requests for appointments by exception to the Senior Civil Service turned down by the Civil Service Commission since 2010; and who was appointed for each such post.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105929","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-06","<p>This information is included in Freedom of Information statistics published on the Internet:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics#2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics#2014</a></p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-06T14:30:24.3418264Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105929/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105929/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many Freedom of Information requests her Department has declined to answer in full since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105930","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-10","<p>The core department has made 219 appointments by exception to the Civil Service Recruitment Principles for the period 1 April 2010- 31 March 2014.</p><p>This covers 66 temporary appointments, 18 secondments, 25 transfers of staff from other public bodies, 103 transferred as a consequence of TUPE and 7 conversions to permanency.</p><p>The cost of identifying each individual appointed would be disproportionate and names cannot be provided as to do so would not be fair processing of personal data.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-10T12:29:46.0389457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105930/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105930/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, on how many occasions her Department has made appointments by exception since 2010; and who was appointed for each such post.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105931","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-06","<p>iPhones are not approved devices for use in Core Defra. The Department has therefore incurred no spend.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-06T14:25:40.8708298Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105931/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105931/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105931/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-03","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department spent on iPhones in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105932","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-10","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) has purchased one iPhone with central FCO funds. Records of purchases using devolved FCO budgets (i.e. those managed by our overseas diplomatic missions or departments in London) are not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-11-10T14:40:03.0824618Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105932/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105932/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105932/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-03","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much his Department spent on iPhones in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105933","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-10","The Civil Service Recruitment Principles require recruitment to the Civil Service to be on the basis of merit after fair and open competition. Recruitment is also permitted, without fair and open competition, in an established set of circumstances (‘Exceptions’), when it has not been possible – or it is impracticable or disproportionate given an urgent need for business critical skills - to select someone on merit through fair and open competition. This has been our interpretation of ‘exceptions’ in the context of this question. The following table shows the number of times the Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) has made use of these exceptions by financial year since 2010. FY 2007/8-103 FY 2008/9-52 FY 2009/10-33 FY 2010/11-15 FY 2011/2012-36 FY 2012/2013-14 FY 2013/2014-25 FY 2014/2015 (to 5/11/14)-15 The figures cover recruitment in the UK where an individual has been identified as as offering particular skills or experience which are critical to the business of the organisation. The FCO does not publish details of staff members.","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-11-10T17:39:38.9985094Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105933/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105933/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-03","Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, on how many occasions his Department has made appointments by exception since 2010; and who was appointed for each such post.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105934","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-10","<p>The Ministry of Justice (MOJ) publishes a quarterly statistics bulletin concerning FOI responses from all Government Departments including The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO). The bulletin includes tables showing how many requests were granted in full, or resulted in some information being withheld or all information withheld. The MOJ statistics bulletin can be found at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-11-10T15:42:50.2114704Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105934/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105934/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105934/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many Freedom of Information requests his Department has declined to answer in full since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213087"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105935","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-07","<p>At the Gaza reconstruction conference on 12 October, which I attended alongside the Minister of State for International Development, the UK pledged £20m.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-11-07T11:34:51.5973653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105935/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105935/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105935/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-03","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much money was pledged by the UK Government at the recent International Donor Conference for Gaza held in Egypt.","false","Biography information for Mr Frank Roy","Motherwell and Wishaw","Mr Frank Roy","213121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105936","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-07","<p>I issued a statement on 29 October condemning the announcement of plans for 1,060 new housing units in East Jerusalem. I made it clear that this was an ill-judged and ill-timed decision, which makes it harder to achieve a two state solution with Jerusalem as a shared capital. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv have raised this issue with the Israeli National Security Adviser, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs Political-Military Adviser, senior contacts at the National Security Council and the Cabinet Office.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-11-07T11:24:18.228363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105936/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105936/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/105936/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-03","Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he last discussed with his Israeli counterpart the planned building of 1,000 new houses in Jerusalem.","false","Biography information for Mr Frank Roy","Motherwell and Wishaw","Mr Frank Roy","213120"
