"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106115","Wales Office","false","2014-11-10","<p>The Ministry of Justice (MoJ) publish annual statistical reports on the handling of requests for information under the Freedom of Information Act 2000 for central government. The Wales Office submits quarterly and annual returns to the MoJ. The published reports include statistics on requests that have been refused in full. These reports can be accessed via the following webpage:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2014-11-10T11:17:02.24719Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106115/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106115/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106115/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-11-03","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many Freedom of Information requests his Department has declined to answer in full since 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","213097"
