"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102018","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-11-10","<p>This is an issue which the Higher Education sector takes very seriously and where institutions have clear policies in place.</p><p>Institutions are supported in this area by the work of Plagiarism Advice (<a href="http://www.plagiarismadvice.org/" target="_blank">www.plagiarismadvice.org</a>) which was established to address concerns about plagiarism and the authenticity of student work. The sanctions that universities are able to apply to students who attempt to pass off work as their own, when it is not, are serious and significant.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","212580","2014-11-10T14:09:25.7588637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102018/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102018/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102018/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-31","Students: Plagiarism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department has (a) considered and (b) taken to ensure that businesses advertising assignment writing services clearly state the potential ramifications for students of portraying such materials as their own work.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","212825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102019","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-11-05","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills does not hold any central data on the number and location of staff on secondment.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-11-05T15:49:13.9789265Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102019/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102019/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102019/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-31","Big Society Network and Society Network Foundation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many civil servants or special advisers his Department seconded to (a) the Big Society Network and (b) the Society Network Foundation between 2010 and 2014.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","212833"
