"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102029","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-07","<p>The first three Astute class submarines were ordered as a single batch. It is therefore not possible to identify separately the construction costs for Artful. The planned date of handover of Artful to the Royal Navy is August 2015.</p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-11-07T14:13:13.676342Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102029/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102029/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102029/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-31","HMS Artful","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) predicted and (b) actual cost to the public purse was of the construction of HMS Artful; and what the (i) predicted and (ii) actual date of handover of HMS Artful to the Royal Navy was.","false","Biography information for Mr Mike Hancock","Portsmouth South","Mr Mike Hancock","212799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102030","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-11","<p>The information requested in respect of the Naval Service is provided in the table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Number of personnel dismissed for drug-related offences</p></td><td><p>Number of personnel dismissed for the possession or use of cannabis</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014 (to 3 November)</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The information has been compiled using the date of conviction, not the date of offence. It does not include administrative discharges and therefore compulsory drug test failures are not included.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-11T17:26:37.9005884Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102030/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102030/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102030/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-31","Armed Forces: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many members of the Royal Navy were dismissed for drug-related offences in the last three years; and how many such dismissals were for possession or use of cannabis.","false","Biography information for Mr Mike Hancock","Portsmouth South","Mr Mike Hancock","212800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102031","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-10","<p>The table sets out the information requested in respect of the British Army.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Number of British Army personnel dismissed for drug-related offences?</p></td><td><p>Number of British Army personnel dismissed for possession or use of cannabis?</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p><p>(as at 31 Oct)</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The information has been compiled using the date of conviction, not the date of offence. It does not include administrative discharges and therefore compulsory drugs test failures are not included.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-10T17:35:26.13583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102031/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102031/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102031/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-31","Armed Forces: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many members of the British Army were dismissed for drug-related offences in the last three years; and how many such dismissals were for possession or use of cannabis.","false","Biography information for Mr Mike Hancock","Portsmouth South","Mr Mike Hancock","212801"
